### Holy Grail Layout – Target Design
Typical structure jo aapko banana hai:

```
Header (full width)
────────────────────
Sidebar | Main Content
        |
        |
Footer (full width)
```

### Recommended CSS Solution (Step-by-Step)

```css
/* 1. Grid Container */
.holy-grail {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr;     /* Sidebar + Main */
  grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto;    /* Header + Content + Footer */
  min-height: 100vh;
  gap: 20px;
}

/* 2. Using Line-based Placement */
.header {
  grid-column: 1 / -1;        /* Full width (line 1 se last line tak) */
}

.sidebar {
  grid-column: 1 / 2;         /* First column */
}

.main {
  grid-column: 2 / 3;         /* Second column */
}

.footer {
  grid-column: 1 / -1;        /* Full width */
}
```

### Alternative (Using grid-template-areas – Cleaner)

```css
.holy-grail {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-areas:
    "header"
    "sidebar main"
    "footer";
  grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr;
  grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto;
  gap: 20px;
  min-height: 100vh;
}

.header   { grid-area: header; }
.sidebar  { grid-area: sidebar; }
.main     { grid-area: main; }
.footer   { grid-area: footer; }
```

### Responsive Tip (Mobile pe)
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .holy-grail {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    grid-template-areas:
      "header"
      "main"
      "sidebar"
      "footer";
  }
}
```

